<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="population-n">population <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /ˌpɒpju'leɪʃn/    美 /ˌpɑːpju'leɪʃn/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>人口；人口数量：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a country with the ageing population 
人口老龄化的国家</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The Bai ethnic group has a population of around two million, 90% of whom live in Yunnan. 
白族人口大约有200万，其中的90%居住在云南。</p><footer> 外研⑦ – 5</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(某事物的) 总数；(人的) 全体：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the dolphin population 
海豚总数</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The whole population of the town came out to welcome him. 
整个镇上的居民都出来欢迎他。</p></div>

<p>注: 问“…有多少人口？”时，要使用what，不能用how many或how much；修饰人口多少的形容词不用many或few，而用large或small。  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What is the population of Zhejiang Province? 
浙江省有多少人口？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>China has the largest population in the world. 
世界上中国人口最多。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The population of Jiangsu <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ to more than twice what it was in 1949. The figure is now approaching 74 million. 
  （2009 江苏）<br />
A.has grown<br />
B.have grown<br />
C.grew<br />
D.are growing  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. A  </p></div>